            <title>[CAMEL-6504] org.apache.camel.main.Main#doStop() throws java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6504</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When calling a Camel application with parameter -h all parameters are printed an the program exits.&lt;br/&gt;
But it is no clean exit; it throws an java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason for this is the expression in doStop():&lt;br/&gt;
+&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;getCamelContexts().get(0).stop();&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;get(0) returns null, if no context is initialized yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See camel-users mailinglist, thread &quot;Bug in org.apache.camel.main.Main#doStop() ?&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
